entries.femaleVariant: [Hotwire] I'll bypass the coupling.
Hmmm… Mhuh…
Got any idea what to do?
Did anyone ask your opinion?
[Start engine]
It'll get me to Night City. I'll figure somethin' else out there.
Right...
Hey, Mike. Didn't know you had a customer...
Don't you sweat it, Mike. We're gonna hash it out.
Don'tcha know you owe the sheriff a word when you pay his town a visit? To tell 'im what's brought ya here, maybe even over a cup o' coffee?
I'm here alone.
What do you have against nomads?
There's no clan, there's no camp. I'm here alone.
entries.maleVariant: There is no clan, there is no camp. I'm here alone.

entries.femaleVariant: Are you one of those who believe everything the talkin' heads say? That nomads are the world's greatest evil?
entries.maleVariant: Are you one of those who believe everything the talking heads say? That nomads are the world's greatest evil?

entries.femaleVariant: Ain't buyin' it. Nomads always stick to their packs.
My family's in pieces. That's why I'm headed for Night City.
I'm gonna bypass the coupling and rig a hotwire.
Compressor'll run on and on. Could seize up.
OK, let's see what happens…
The corps pay you and have you on a leash like a dog, you know that?
No. I'm a man that respects order. Corps brought us that order, and I intend for it to stay that way.
Makes you an outcast among outcasts.
I'm just passing through.
No need to worry – I won't be stayin' long.
entries.maleVariant: No need to worry. I won't be stayin' long.

entries.femaleVariant: My mistake. I hadn't planned on stopping. A failed coupling forced my hand.
My mistake.
Name's Andrew Jones. Probably heard of me.
Didn't answer my question, now, did ya?
I can't say that I have.
Yeah, always some failure 'hind mistakes.
Served in spec ops during the last war. "Silver Shoguns"... ring any bells?
I can't say that it does.
Don't like to get along, do ya?
That a nomad vehicle? Mighta expected that…
I'll just fix it and be on my way.
If you have a problem, I'm willin' to hear it.
I'll just fix it up and go. I've no reason to linger.
entries.maleVariant: I'll just fix it and go, I've no reason to linger.

entries.femaleVariant: Do you have a problem?
Ahhh, nope, ya sure as shit don't.
Lemme tell ya what my problem is.
Nothin' boils my blood like a fuckin' stray.
Where'd your clan pitch camp?
Mhm. But you don't wanna see me bare my fangs, so I'll ask again – where's your clan?
I need to use your radio tower.
I saw a broadcast and comms tower on my way in. My antenna's down, and I need to radio someone.
What you need's to hightail it outta here without another word.
You're a real hospitable bunch.
I heard this place was famous for its hospitality. Aw, glad to see it wasn't just rumors.
entries.maleVariant: I heard this place was famous for its hospitality. Glad to see it wasn't just rumors.

entries.femaleVariant: You're damn right we are – when people come along who know how to behave.
Electric coupling module.
You said it was nothing serious when I came in. You said you were sure.
Guess I was wrong.
I'm 'onna pay you what we agreed. Not one enny more.
entries.maleVariant: I'm gonna pay you what we agreed. Not one enny more.

entries.femaleVariant: Huh. For that you can borrow my tools and fix it yourself.
Can always look for another shop where they won't ask a lone nomad why she's huggin' the border.
entries.maleVariant: Can always look for another shop where they won't ask a lone nomad why he's huggin' the border.

entries.femaleVariant: That's fine. Step aside.
Not shabby at all. Question's how long it'll last ya.
Uh, ro-rolled in a-a few hours past. I... I thought she'd at least called into ya.
entries.maleVariant: Uh, ro-rolled in a few hours past. I... I… I thought, er, he'd at least called into ya.

entries.femaleVariant: Sure as hell hope you'll be on your way before long…
Ain't got no mind to see you driftin' around these parts. Got it?
[Connect to radio station]
Mmm…
So, doable? It sure was.
Antenna on this heap don't seem like it packs a punch. Not liable to hear much.
Satisficing, that – not a solid fix. Might as well have used spit and duct tape.
Doable? Doable.
You don't say…
It worked – that's what matters.
[Remove patch]
[Check engine] Step aside. I'll handle it.
[Get in]
You like the sound of your voice, don't you?
[Close door] I don't want any trouble.
I've made it clear – I don't want any trouble.
[Close door] You like the sound of your voice, don't you?
Then stop lookin' for it and hit the road, quick.
What's that, drifter? What're you on about?
Nothin', nothin' at all.
Hm, yeah. Best that way.
I'm thinking.
What?
I said step aside. I'll handle it.
I'm thinkin', I'm thinkin'…
Mmh. And?
And your chirping is not helping.
Nope.
Afraid not.
It's like I was tellin' ya…
No, no…
[Start engine]
[Start engine]
I'm going to pay you what we agreed.
Y'know, I don't have all day.
You're wearin' on my patience now.
What, suddenly all shy?
Hey, I'm talkin' to you.
Heh. It die on you after all?
I'm lookin' for someone – Jackie Welles? Have you maybe--?
I'm looking for Jackie Welles.
Did anyone ask your opinion?
